Sometimes happens that development branch affects more than one component, and it's driven by dedicated person (or a team). It might be reflected in JIRA as specific version, like "v2", or "next". Issues related to that version should by default go to the person who is doing those changes (version lead), not current maintainers of previous version components.

So my proposal is to add support for version-based default assignee. To avoid conflicts with component-based default assignee it should be also possible to set priorities between those. So for v1 issues would go to component lead, and for v2 it would be version lead who gets the issues by default.

